communities,&#3; parentsâ€”are&#3; then&#3; involved&#3; in&#3; monitoring&#3; those&#3; central&#3; budgetary&#3; allocations.&#3; School&#3;
autonomy&#3; in&#3; the&#3; planning&#3; and&#3; management&#3; of&#3; the&#3; school&#3; budget&#3; is&#3; considered&#3; desirable&#3; because&#3; it&#3; can&#3;
increase&#3; the&#3; efficiency&#3; of&#3; financial&#3; resources,&#3; give&#3; schools&#3; more&#3; flexibility&#3; in&#3; budget&#3; management,&#3; and&#3;
give&#3;parents&#3;the&#3;opportunity&#3;to&#3;have&#3;more&#3;voice&#3;on&#3;budget&#3;planning&#3;and&#3;execution.&#3;Greater&#3;autonomy&#3;at&#3;
the&#3;school&#3;level&#3;helps&#3;schools&#3;fight&#3;for&#3;central&#3;resources&#3;since&#3; they&#3;can&#3;use&#3; the&#3;indicators&#3;of&#3;assessment&#3;
to&#3;render&#3;accounts&#3;of&#3;student&#3;performance&#3;and&#3;in&#3;the&#3;process&#3;use&#3;moral&#3;suasion&#3;to&#3;get&#3;increased&#3;funding&#3;
from&#3;the&#3;central&#3;level.&#3;&#3;&#3;
