The&#3;Systems&#3;Approach&#3;for&#3;Better&#3;Education&#3;Results&#3;(SABER)&#3;initiative&#3;collects&#3;data&#3;
on&#3; the&#3; policies&#3; and&#3; institutions&#3; of&#3; education&#3; systems&#3; around&#3; the&#3; world&#3; and&#3;
benchmarks&#3; them&#3; against&#3; practices&#3; associated&#3; with&#3; student&#3; learning.&#3; SABER&#3; aims&#3;
to&#3; give&#3; all&#3; parties&#3; with&#3; a&#3; stake&#3; in&#3; educational&#3; resultsâ€”from&#3; students,&#3;
administrators,&#3; teachers,&#3; and&#3; parents&#3; to&#3; policymakers,&#3; business&#3; people&#3; and&#3;
political&#3; leadersâ€”an&#3; accessible,&#3; detailed,&#3; objective&#3; snapshot&#3; of&#3; how&#3; well&#3; the&#3;
policies&#3;of&#3;their&#3;countryâ€™s&#3;education&#3;system&#3;are&#3;oriented&#3;toward&#3;delivering&#3;learning&#3;
for&#3;all&#3;children&#3;and&#3;youth.&#3;

This&#3;framework&#3;paper&#3;focuses&#3;specifically&#3;in&#3;the&#3;area&#3;of&#3;School&#3;Autonomy&#3;and&#3;
Accountability&#3;Sector.&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;&#3;




The&#3;findings,&#3;interpretations,&#3;and&#3;conclusions&#3;expressed&#3;herein&#3;are&#3;those&#3;of&#3;the&#3;author(s)&#3;and&#3;do&#3;not&#3;necessarily&#3;reflect&#3;the&#3;
views&#3;of&#3;the&#3;International&#3;Bank&#3;for&#3;Reconstruction&#3;and&#3;Development&#3;/&#3;The&#3;World&#3;Bank&#3;Group&#3;and&#3;its&#3;affiliated&#3;organizations,&#3;
or&#3;those&#3;of&#3;the&#3;Executive&#3;Director&#3;of&#3;the&#3;World&#3;Bank&#3;Group&#3;or&#3;the&#3;governments&#3;they&#3;represent.&#3;

The&#3; World&#3; Bank&#3; Group&#3; does&#3; not&#3; guarantee&#3; the&#3; accuracy&#3; of&#3; the&#3; data&#3; included&#3; in&#3; this&#3; work.&#3; The&#3; boundaries,&#3; colors,&#3;
denominations,&#3;and&#3;other&#3;information&#3;shown&#3;on&#3;any&#3;map&#3;in&#3;this&#3;work&#3;do&#3;not&#3;imply&#3;and&#3;judgment&#3;on&#3;the&#3;part&#3;of&#3;the&#3;World&#3;
